A BILL TO BE ENTITLED
AN ACT
1 To amend Title 37 of the Official Code of Georgia Annotated, relating to mental health, so
2 as to provide for a five-year pilot program for the purpose of creating emergency psychiatric
3 assessment, treatment, and healing units or EmPATH units in hospitals; to provide for
4 definitions; to provide for a short title; to provide for the administration of such program; to
5 provide for rules and regulations; to provide for the certification of EmPATH units; to
6 provide for an appropriations contingency; to provide for funding or gifts in-kind; to provide
7 for exclusions; to provide for termination of such program and automatic repeal of the article;
8 to provide for related matters; to repeal conflicting laws; and for other purposes.
9 BE IT ENACTED BY THE GENERAL ASSEMBLY OF GEORGIA:
10 SECTION 1.
11 Title 37 of the Official Code of Georgia Annotated, relating to mental health, is amended in
12 Chapter 1, relating to the governing and regulation of mental health, by adding a new article
13 to read as follows:
