14 "ARTICLE 8
15 37-1-130.
16 This article shall be known and may be cited as the 'EmPATH Georgia Act.'
17 37-1-131.
18 As used in this article, the term:
19 (1) 'Behavioral health crisis' has the same meaning as in Code Section 37-12-1.
20 (2) 'Behavioral health services' means services which are designed to prevent or
21 ameliorate the effects of mental or emotional illness or addictive disease.
22 (3) 'Emergency psychiatric assessment, treatment, and healing unit' or 'EmPATH unit'
23 means a hospital based outpatient program that:
24 (A) Operates for the purpose of providing behavioral health services for individuals
25 experiencing a behavioral health crisis;
26 (B) Provides brief, intensive crisis treatment that shall include an evaluation by a
27 psychiatrist within 24 hours of an individual's admission;
28 (C) Provides other appropriate treatment or services as necessary, including, but not
29 limited to, observation, detoxification, and stabilization services, and medication
30 prescribed by a physician;
31 (D) Provides services 24 hours a day, seven days a week to individuals on a voluntary
32 and involuntary basis in a community based setting as an alternative to emergency
33 department admission, inpatient hospitalization, and other higher levels of care; and
34 (E) Is certified by the department and complies with applicable standards.
35 (4) 'Rural county' means a county having a population of less than 50,000 according to
36 the United States decennial census of 2020 or any future such census.
37 (5) 'Urban county' means a county having a population equal to or greater than 50,000
38 according to the United States decennial census of 2020 or any future such census.
