39 37-1-132.
40 (a) The department, in coordination with the Department of Community Health, shall
41 establish a pilot program to provide grants and funding for the creation, development, and
42 operation of EmPATH units.
43 (b) The department, in coordination with the Department of Community Health, shall
44 promulgate rules and regulations for EmPATH units, which shall include, but not be
45 limited to, minimum care, facility operational, and reporting requirements. Such rules and
46 regulations shall endeavor to adhere to the most recently established, medically recognized
47 EmPATH model.
48 (c) The department, in coordination with the Department of Community Health, shall
49 establish grant criteria and make award decisions; provided, however, that at least one
50 EmPATH unit shall be established in a rural county and at least one EmPATH unit shall
51 be established in an urban county. Grants shall not be used to fund existing programs.
52 37-1-133.
53 (a) An EmPATH unit shall be designated as an emergency receiving facility under Code
54 Sections 37-3-40 and 37-7-40 and an evaluating facility under Code Sections 37-3-60
55 and 37-7-60, but shall not be designated as a treatment facility under Code Section 37-3-80
56 or 37-7-80.
57 (b) The department shall be authorized to certify EmPATH units pursuant to this article.
58 37-1-134.
59 (a) Any program certified as a crisis stabilization unit pursuant to this article shall be
60 exempt from the requirements to obtain a certificate of need pursuant to Article 3 of
61 Chapter 6 of Title 31.
62 (b) This Code section is not intended to and should not be construed to affect the services
63 offered by a crisis stabilization unit as defined in Code Section 37-1-29.
