64 37-1-135.
65 (a) This article shall be subject to appropriation to the department from the General
66 Assembly specifically for such pilot program. The department and the Department of
67 Community Health may accept and solicit private funding, public grants, in-kind gifts, or
68 any other funding or donations that may be available to facilitate the purpose of the grant
69 program.
70 (b) No later than December 31, 2029, the department shall submit a detailed written report
71 on the implementation and effectiveness of such pilot program to the Governor, the
72 Speaker of the House of Representatives, the President of the Senate, and the chairpersons
73 of the House Committee on Health and the Senate Health and Human Services Committee.
74 Such report shall also include recommendations as to expansion of such pilot program state
75 wide.
76 (c) The pilot program created by this article shall terminate five years after such program's
77 start date, and this article shall be repealed by operation of law on July 1 of the year
78 following the conclusion of such pilot program."
79 SECTION 2.
80 Said title is further amended in Article 7 of Chapter 3, relating to adult residential mental
81 health services licensing, by revising paragraph (1) of Code Section 37-3-202, relating to
82 definitions, as follows:
83 "(1) 'Adult residential mental health program' means a subacute residential alternative
84 service of four or more residential beds authorized to provide psychiatric services for
85 mentally ill persons 18 years of age or older that operates 24 hours per day, (7) seven
86 days per week to provide intensive short-term noninstitutional treatment to individuals
87 who are temporarily in need of a 24-hour-per-day supportive therapeutic setting for
88 prevention of or transition from or after acute psychiatric hospitalization. Such term shall
89 not include crisis stabilization units, as defined in Code Section 37-1-29; community
